  i)Write a Jenkins pipeline script to checkout code from a GitHub repository and display the list of files in the workspace
         ans::
         pipeline {
         agent any
         stages {
         stage('Checkout Code') {
         steps {
         git branch:'main',url:'https://github.com/kavyathatavarthi/exp1-cli.git'
         }
         }
         stage('Show Files') {
         steps {
         bat 'dir'
         }
         }
         }
        }
   ii)Write a Jenkins pipeline script to checkout code from a GitHub repository and print the current working directory in Jenkins workspace.
        ans::
         pipeline {
         agent any
         stages {
          stage('Checkout Code') {
           steps {
            git branch: 'main', url: 'https://github.com/kavyathatavarthi/exp1-cli.git'
           }
          }
          stage('Print Directory') {
           steps {
            bat 'cd'
           }
          }
         }
        }
  iii)Write a Jenkins pipeline script to checkout code from a GitHub repository and print a success message after execution.
